org.cast.cwm.xml
Class XmlSection

java.lang.Object
  org.cast.cwm.xml.XmlSection
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, Comparable<XmlSection>, IXmlPointer
public class XmlSection
extends Object
implements IXmlPointer, Serializable, Comparable<XmlSection>

Represents a section of an XML document. A "section" in this case means a structural element, such as a chapter or page.

init

public void init(XmlDocument document,
                 XmlSection parent,
                 String id,
                 Element elt,
                 String title)
Set up an XmlSection with the basic values.

Parameters:
document - the parent XmlDocument, not to be confused with Document
parent - the parent XmlSection, or null if this is the root
id - the Id of this section (root Id is DOCUMENT_ID)
elt - the DOM element of this section
title - the title of this section (XmlParser implementation determines what this value is)

public List<? extends Serializable> getLabels()
